NLquery: For each Internet Service(sid) find the most frequently used version among all Base Models that utilize it
prompt: Write SQL to find the most common version for each service ID
LLM_returned_SQL_query: SELECT sid version COUNT(*) as usage_count FROM ModelServices GROUP BY sid version HAVING COUNT(*) = (SELECT MAX(cnt) FROM (SELECT COUNT(*) as cnt FROM ModelServices ms2 WHERE ms2.sid = ModelServices.sid GROUP BY version) sub) ORDER BY sid

NLquery: For each Internet Service(sid) find the most frequently used version among all Base Models that utilize it
prompt: Given table ModelServices(bmid sid version) find the mode version for each sid
LLM_returned_SQL_query: SELECT ms1.sid ms1.version COUNT(*) as usage_count FROM ModelServices ms1 GROUP BY ms1.sid ms1.version HAVING COUNT(*) >= ALL (SELECT COUNT(*) FROM ModelServices ms2 WHERE ms2.sid = ms1.sid GROUP BY ms2.version) ORDER BY ms1.sid

NLquery: Find all the Internet Service(sid) that are utilized by any Base Model built by the agent creator user_iuwrh (Note: Changed from every to any because original question with every returns empty set in test data)
prompt: Find all services used by base models from creator user_iuwrh
LLM_returned_SQL_query: SELECT DISTINCT ms.sid FROM ModelServices ms JOIN BaseModel bm ON ms.bmid = bm.bmid JOIN AgentCreator ac ON bm.creator_uid = ac.uid JOIN Users u ON ac.uid = u.uid WHERE u.username = 'user_iuwrh' ORDER BY ms.sid

NLquery: Find all the Internet Service(sid) that are utilized by any Base Model built by the agent creator user_iuwrh (Note: Changed from every to any because original question with every returns empty set in test data)
prompt: List unique service IDs for models created by user_iuwrh
LLM_returned_SQL_query: SELECT ms.sid FROM ModelServices ms WHERE ms.bmid IN (SELECT bm.bmid FROM BaseModel bm JOIN AgentCreator ac ON bm.creator_uid = ac.uid JOIN Users u ON ac.uid = u.uid WHERE u.username = 'user_iuwrh') GROUP BY ms.sid ORDER BY ms.sid

NLquery: Find all customized models(mid) that do not appear in model configurations
prompt: Find customized model IDs not used in any configuration
LLM_returned_SQL_query: SELECT mid FROM CustomizedModel WHERE (bmid mid) NOT IN (SELECT bmid mid FROM ModelConfigurations)

NLquery: Find all customized models(mid) that do not appear in model configurations
prompt: Using LEFT JOIN find unused customized models
LLM_returned_SQL_query: SELECT cm.mid FROM CustomizedModel cm LEFT JOIN ModelConfigurations mc ON cm.bmid = mc.bmid AND cm.mid = mc.mid WHERE mc.cid IS NULL
